	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64505919"><p>My first printer was an Epson MX80 in 1981. It had a parallel port but I don't remember if it was commonly called a "Centronics" port yet. All the computer mags at the time seemed to offer Epson and Gorilla Banana (name still craps me up) dot matrix printers. I don't ever remember seeing a "Centronics" branded printer.  Regardless I had to build a serial to parallel converter to use it with my system at the time.</p></div>
