		<div id="comment_body_64505833">That's right. Hangul is an excellent writing system. Korean can be written in a mixture of Chinese characters and the Hangul alphabet (basically, with Chinese characters used to write the many loans from Chinese, and Hangul used to write native Korean words, loans from languages other than Chinese, and the grammatical affixes), and you will find this in older publications, especially academic ones. The current trend in South Korea is to use Chinese characters very little, almost entirely for names of instit</div>
	</div>

