	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64505949">Pinyin is a phonetic system for writing Mandarin Chinese. There are other roman systems for other varieties of Chinese. One input method for Chinese is to type in pinyin with the system offering you a ranked list of Chinese characters from which you choose. There are, however, a number of other input methods. Another, used mostly in Taiwan, is based on "bopomofo", a non-roman method of writing Chinese phonetically which is taught to school children in Taiwan and used to give them the pronunciations of Chine</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64505949">

